{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Development Journey Tracker",
  "description": "After each agent session, appends a dated entry to DEVELOPMENT_JOURNEY.md summarizing what was done, what changed, and why. Also cleans up temporary files created during tasks (SQL scripts, backup files, debug scripts, one-off test files, etc.) to keep the root tidy.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "\nYou are the project historian for GAS-MIS (Go Ahead Security Management Information System). Your job is to:\n\n1. **Update DEVELOPMENT_JOURNEY.md** — Append a new dated entry summarizing this session.\n2. **Clean up temporary files** — Delete files that were created as one-off task artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## STEP 1 — Update DEVELOPMENT_JOURNEY.md\n\nRead the file `DEVELOPMENT_JOURNEY.md` (create it if it doesn't exist yet, seeding it from `PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION.md` context).\n\nThen append a new entry at the TOP of the journey log (most recent first) using this format:\n\n```\n---\n## [DATE] — [Short session title, e.g. \"Bulk Invoice Export Fix\"]\n\n### What was done\n- Bullet list of changes made this session\n\n### Files changed\n- List of files created, modified, or deleted\n\n### Why\n- Brief explanation of the business or technical reason\n\n### Notes\n- Any gotchas, decisions made, or things to watch out for\n---\n```\n\nUse today's date. Infer the session title and content from:\n- The conversation history and tool calls made in this session\n- Any new or modified `.md` files in the root (they are named after the feature/fix)\n- Any source files that were edited\n\nIf `DEVELOPMENT_JOURNEY.md` does not exist yet, create it with a header section first:\n```\n# GAS-MIS — Development Journey\n\nThis file is the living record of the GAS-MIS development journey, maintained automatically after each Kiro session.\n\n**Project**: Go Ahead Security Management Information System  \n**Stack**: React 18 + TypeScript + Electron + SQLite + Tailwind CSS  \n**Language**: French (UI), English (code)  \n**Started**: [earliest date you can infer from existing MD files]\n\n---\n```\nThen append the first entry below it.\n\n---\n\n## STEP 2 — Clean up temporary files\n\nAfter updating the journey, delete files that match these patterns (they are one-off task artifacts, not permanent project files):\n\n**Delete if they exist:**\n- `database-cleanup.sql` — one-off cleanup script\n- `database_backup_*.sqlite` — database backup files (keep `database.sqlite`)\n- `electron_backup_*.cjs` — Electron backup files\n- `electron_main_backup_*.js` — Electron main backup files  \n- `preload_backup_*.cjs` — preload backup files\n- `browser-test-*.js` — browser test scripts\n- `debug-*.js` — debug scripts\n- `fix-*.js` — one-off fix scripts\n- `test-*.js` and `test-*.cjs` — standalone test scripts in root (NOT in `tests/` folder)\n- `generate-*.cjs` — one-off SQL generation scripts\n- `import-*.sql` — one-off import SQL files\n\n**Do NOT delete:**\n- `database.sqlite` — the live database\n- `*.md` files — documentation (they feed the journey)\n- Any file inside `src/`, `tests/`, `scripts/`, `public/`, `electron/`, `supabase/`\n- `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `eslint.config.js`, `tailwind.config.js`, `postcss.config.js`, `vite.config.ts`, `vitest.config.ts`, `tsconfig*.json`, `index.html`\n- `.gitignore`, `README.md`\n\nFor each file you delete, note it in the \"Files changed\" section of the journey entry under a \"🧹 Cleaned up\" sub-bullet.\n\nBe conservative — if you are unsure whether a file is safe to delete, skip it and note it in the journey entry instead.\n"
  }
}